<section xml:id="active-code_c-and-c">
  <title>C and C++</title>
  <p>Now for the most famous program of all time! This program is often the first program someone will write in a new language. Here it is presented in the original C language!</p>
  <program xml:id="hw_in_c" interactive="activecode" language="c">
    <input>
         #include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

         int main() {
         printf("Hello World!");
         }
         </input>
  </program>
  <p>You can also have C++ code in an activecode.</p>
  <program xml:id="lc2" interactive="activecode" language="cpp">
    <input>
         #include &lt;iostream&gt;
         using namespace std;
         int main() {
         cout &lt;&lt; "Hello World!" &lt;&lt; endl; cout &lt;&lt; "Welcome to C++ Programming" &lt;&lt; endl;
         }
         </input>
  </program>
  <hint>
    <program language="rst">
      <input>
.. activecode:: lc2
            :language: cpp
            :stdin: 100
            :compileargs: ['-std=c++11', '-Wall', '-Wpedantic']

            #include &lt;iostream&gt;
            using namespace std;
            int main() {
            cout &lt;&lt; "Hello World!" &lt;&lt; endl; cout &lt;&lt; "Welcome to C++ Programming" &lt;&lt; endl;
            }
</input>
    </program>
  </hint>
</section>
